Subject: [PATCH] diagnosability: live IN FLIGHT builtin activity + 5-minute
 stall watchdog
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A stuck box had no 'running builtins' view — processes have a tree,
but an in-process make/recipe/$(shell) spinning silently was
invisible. Now:

- kati keeps a per-thread activity registry (RAII guards around each
  recipe, $(shell CMD), and dependency analysis — nesting restores
  the enclosing entry).
- the box ships an activity snapshot to the engine every 30s
  (box_activity frame → live BoxState, ephemeral); review.box_summary
  merges it, and the box overview renders an '── IN FLIGHT ──'
  section: each busy builtin with its live age, red at 5+ minutes.
- a watchdog (SARUN_STALL_SECS, default 300) also prints
  '*kati*: STALL? Ns without completing: <what>' to the box's stderr
  — nothing in the build may run 5+ minutes in silence. Standalone
  rkati gets the stderr watchdog too.

Both corpora fail=0; make-rs PASS.

